When parsing our dhcpd.leases file the library was crashing on a record because it has the hardware field but not he ends field, so it tries to construct and fails with a KeyError [here](https://github.com/MartijnBraam/python-isc-dhcp-leases/blob/310e61bbba54e789453161961d66f1eaad6f382b/isc_dhcp_leases/iscdhcpleases.py#L209)
```python
        if properties['ends'] == 'never':
```

lease 172.23.251.150 {
  starts 4 2015/09/10 00:29:00;
  tstp 4 2015/09/10 00:28:44;
  tsfp 4 2015/09/10 00:29:00;
  atsfp 4 2015/09/10 00:29:00;
  binding state free;
  hardware ethernet 00:21:cc:06:94:e9;
  uid "\001\000!\314\006\224\351";
}

